Music Malaysia the generic term for music that has been created various genres Malaysia great variety genres Malaysian music reflect the specific cultural groups within multiethnic Malaysian society Malay Chinese Indian Dayak KadazanDusun Bajau Orang Asli Melanau Kristang and others general music Malaysia may categorised classical folk syncretic acculturated music popular and contemporary art music Classical and folk music emerged during the precolonial period and exists the form vocal dance and theatrical music such Nobat Mak Yong Mak Inang Dikir barat Ulek mayang and Menora The syncretic music developed during the postPortuguese period 16th century and contains elements from both local music and foreign elements Arabian Persian Indian Chinese and Western musical and theatrical sources Among genres this music are Zapin Ghazal Dondang Sayang Matakantiga Joget Jikey Boria and Bangsawan Both Malaysian popular music and contemporary art music are essentially Westernbased music combined with some local elements 1950s the musician Ramlee helped creating Malaysian music that combined folks songs with Western dance rhythms and western Asian music Besides Malay music Chinese and Indian Malaysians have their own forms music and the indigenous tribes Peninsula and East Malaysia have unique traditional instruments Traditional Malay music spans from music for various theatrical forms such wayang kulit bangsawan and dance dramas well storytelling folk songs and music for dances royal ceremonies martial arts silat life cycle events and religious occasions Many forms traditional Malay music and performing arts appear have originated the KelantanPattani region with influence from India China Thailand and Indonesia The music based around percussion instruments the most important which the gendang drum There are least types traditional drums including kompang and hadrah drums Drums and other traditional percussion instruments are often made from natural materials Besides drums other 